{
  "summary": "Fixed a testing compatibility issue where integration tests dependent on the `analysis` feature failed when running `cargo test --no-default-features`. I added `#![cfg(feature = \"analysis\")]` to all test files in `crates/tokmd/tests/` that invoke subcommands strictly gated by this feature (like `analyze`, `badge`, `baseline`, `gate`, and `run`).",
  "why": "When the `--no-default-features` flag is passed to `cargo test`, the `analysis` feature is disabled in the `tokmd` crate. The CLI router correctly bails with \"analysis feature is not enabled\", but the integration tests executing these subcommands expected success or specific metric outputs. This resulted in false-positive test failures during matrix testing.",
  "evidence": [
    "Running `cargo test -p tokmd --no-default-features` panicked in `crates/tokmd/tests/analyze_integration.rs` with `tokmd analyze failed: ExitStatus(unix_wait_status(256))`",
    "Running `cargo test -p tokmd --no-default-features` panicked in `crates/tokmd/tests/badge_integration.rs` with `tokmd badge --metric lines` returning `Error: analysis feature is not enabled`"
  ],
